Livvic Thin Regular (Livvic-Thin.ttf)

STAT

static font

Variable font must have a STAT table.

No check of STAT table for static fonts included, yet. Static fonts do not need to have a STAT table. It is only recommended by Microsoft, not required.
More infos here:
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/stat

No check of STAT table for static fonts included, yet. Static fonts do not need to have a STAT table. It is only recommended by Microsoft, not required.
More infos here:
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/stat

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Livvic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Livvic Thin'.

Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Livvic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'Livvic Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Livvic Thin Italic (Livvic-ThinItalic.ttf)

Livvic ExtraLight Regular (Livvic-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Livvic-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Pass

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Livvic-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

Livvic ExtraLight Italic (Livvic-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Livvic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'Livvic ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Livvic Light Regular (Livvic-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Livvic-Light', Everything looks good.

Pass

NID 6 is 'Livvic-Light', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Livvic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Livvic Light'.

Pass

Livvic Regular (Livvic-Regular.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Livvic-Regular', Everything looks good.

Pass

NID 6 is 'Livvic-Regular', Everything looks good.

Livvic Medium Regular (Livvic-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Livvic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Livvic Medium'.

Livvic Medium Italic (Livvic-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Livvic-MediumItalic', Everything looks good.

Livvic Medium Italic (Livvic-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Livvic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Livvic Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Livvic-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Livvic SemiBold Regular (Livvic-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

'space' in NID 6 cause issues in fontbook for Mac.

NID 6 is 'Livvic-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Livvic SemiBold Regular (Livvic-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Livvic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Livvic SemiBold'.

Pass

Livvic Bold (Livvic-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Livvic-Bold', Everything looks good.

Livvic Black Regular (Livvic-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Livvic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Livvic Black'.

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Livvic-BlackItalic', Everything looks good.

Livvic Black Italic (Livvic-BlackItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Livvic' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black Italic' = NID 1 'Livvic Black' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.
